Description: Roman numeral smart clock for Raspberry Pi and Linux desktops
 Pi Smart Clock is a full-screen SDL2 clock with weather panels, alarms,
 NWS-style alerts, and configurable clock faces. The Linux build targets
 Debian 13 (Trixie) and Raspberry Pi OS Trixie.
 .
 User settings live under the XDG Base Directory (~/.config/pi-smart-clock).
 Shipped examples are installed under /usr/share/pi-smart-clock/.